	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><date>Tuesday the 4th day of<lb/> month <add>Hebrew</add></date></p>
				<p><date>1863&#45;4&#63;</date></p>
				<p><sic>greeting</sic> to my beloved<lb/> win<add>&#63;</add> friend <persName>Mr. Isaac</persName><lb/> Finally&#44; I came to a deci&#45;<lb/>sion after investigating<lb/> the circumstances <del>right</del><lb/> on the place and in a <add>&#63;</add><lb/> way. I believe and hope that<lb/> we&#39;ll be able to stay there<lb/> for room and board and for<lb/> telephone calls we&#39;ll pay<lb/> &#40;budget&#41; and except this<lb/> we&#39;ll try to do what is only<lb/> possible with the only<lb/> aim not to bring illegitimate<lb/> children into the nation<lb/> of <placeName>Israel</placeName>.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">2</p>
				<p>trying legally and not<lb/> against the law&#44; even<lb/> although it is with<lb/> regret <del>mo</del> that the<lb/> missing cann&#39;<sic>t</sic> be<lb/> avoided.</p>
				<p>I would insist that<lb/> opinions for and against<lb/> shall be expressed before<lb/> the accident. <date>Monday</date><lb/> I&#39;ll see the gentleman for a couple of<lb/> hours &#38; come to a conclusion with<lb/> him.  I hope to hear from you &#38;<lb/> you will hear from me &#38; you can<lb/> expect by news<add>&#63;</add> from me.</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Your friend who</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">cherishes him  expects him</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Jonah&#44; from the house Bondi</persName></p>
